Tremors can be described as the rhythmic muscle contractions that causes the body part to tremble or shake. They are involuntary and cab affect the head, voice box, arms, torso and legs. Some of the reasons why you might be experiencing this health challenge, the preventive measures and possible treatments “According to a publication by Medical news today” will be discussed in this article.
1) Certain medications can cause hand tremor: some antiviral drugs, seizure medication, cancer drugs such as: thalidomide etc.

2) Enhanced physiological tremor can occur as a result of: stress, overactive thyroid, excess caffeine, fatigue, anxiety, vigorous exercise etc.

3) Some health conditions can cause hand tremor: mercury poisoning, kidney or liver failure, fragile X syndrome, psychiatric conditions etc.
4) Neurological conditions can cause hand tremor: multiple sclerosis, stroke, parkinson’s disease, dystonia, traumatic brain injury etc.

Preventive Measures:
1) Ensure that you treat any underlying health condition.
2) Avoid vigorous exercise.
3) Avoid the excess intake of alcohol.

4) Practice mindful and breathing exercises.
Possible Treatments:
1) Botox.
2) Surgery.
3) Medications.
